out Blackhawks in fifth straight loss|url=https://www.nhl.com/news/chicago-blackhawks-minnesota-wild-game-recap/c-295837404|website=NHL.com|accessdate=19 March 2018|date=10 February 2018}}</ref> He recorded his first NHL point in a 7\u20131 win over the [[Washington Capitals]] on 17 February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Roumeliotis|first1=Charlie|title=Blackhawks end eight-game losing streak with win against Capitals|url=https://www.nhl.com/news/washington-capitals-chicago-blackhawks-game-recap/c-296089476|website=NHL.com|accessdate=19 March 2018|date=18 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March 2019, Dahlstr\u00f6m signed a two-year contract extension with the Blackhawks.<ref>{{cite web |title=RELEASE: Blackhawks agree to extension with Dahlstrom |url=https://www.nhl.com/blackhawks/news/release-blackhawks-agree-to-extension-with-dahlstrom/c-306177702 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=27 March 2019 |date=27 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 1, 2019, Dahlstr\u00f6m was claimed off of waivers by the Winnipeg Jets.\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Regular season]]\n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\"|\n! colspan=\"5\"|[[Playoffs]]\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! GP\n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]]\n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]]\n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]]\n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]]\n! GP\n! G\n! A\n! Pts\n! PIM\n|-\n| 2012\u201313\n| [[Link\u00f6ping HC]]\n| [[J20 SuperElit|J20]]\n| 37 || 5 || 8 || 13 || 12\n| 5 || 1 || 1 || 2 || 4\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 2013\u201314\n| Link\u00f6ping HC\n| J20\n| 23 || 2 || 12 || 14 || 6\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n| [[2013\u201314 SHL season|2013\u201314]]\n| Link\u00f6ping HC\n| [[Swedish Hockey League|SHL]]\n| 12 || 0 || 1 || 1 || 0\n| 14 || 1 || 2 || 3 || 2\n|- bgcolor=